  "texts": [
    "Students with learning disabilities, as well as non-native speakers of national languages will benefit most from natural language models [19].Inclusive learning environments can open the way for academic success among students with disabilities, but ethical concerns and challenges (data privacy, algorithmic bias, etc.)",
    "should be carefully addressed to fully harness the potential of AI tools [55].",
    "Indicatively, biases in the data AI systems are trained, might disadvantage certain groups, and bring inequalities.",
    "Or the digital divide may be widened if students lack access to the AI-powered educational technology tools.",
    "(Other areas of) Teaching and learning supportIntegration of generative AI in higher educational practices was found to improve teaching efficiency, and it also saved time for preparation and feedback provision in assignments [56]."
